The paper deals with the compression of DNA sequences generated by high throughput sequencing technologies, which involves the use of data structures and algorithms commonly used in computer science. The use of a probabilistic de Bruijn Graph is a key aspect of the proposed method, which suggests a connection to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). The paper also mentions the use of compression techniques, which could relate to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method that outperforms existing reference-free methods, which could be of interest to researchers in the sub-categories of cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
